[quote=“Ollie, post:19, topic:267943”][quote author=Mopman link=topic=353724.msg2714520#msg2714520 date=1237547312]
Is it your big toe? They recommend that especially for the big toe you should goto the quack. I didn’t, and it healed, but it’s pretty fucked looking and easy to fuck up from kicking stuff now
[/quote]
no the one next to the big toe, it seems to have healed now, its not wonkey (much) but its just hard to bend, will be like that for a while till fully healed though.

So I was rite, don’t waste hospital time for a broken toe (other than big)…[/quote]

As long as it doesn’t hurt while walking, you don’t have to care about any toe. The big toe is a bit helpful when it comes to balance, but it doesn’t make that much difference.

item.title: I broke my toe
item.dc:creator: @Uriko Uriko
item.description:
@Uriko wrote:

[quote=“Ollie, post:3, topic:267943”][quote author=Yz85Racer link=topic=353724.msg2710387#msg2710387 date=1237262213]
I’ve broken plenty of things. I would go to the doctors though, you can’t be sure. You might of moved plates, or dislodged the socket.
[/quote]
I broke it 2 days ago, its kinda not hurting now, it looks out of place and is wonky… haha…
p.s. im not registered with a doctors here. im at uni…

for toes and stuff they say to just leave them anyway…[/quote]You probably tore the ligaments. Ice it often, try to keep as little pressure as possible on it, and keep it straight. You’re definitely going to want to go to a doctor if you want it to heal properly… After the swelling has gone down, an hour or so every day stretch it (bend it, etc)

item.title: I broke my toe
item.dc:creator: @bootnecklad bootnecklad
item.description:
@bootnecklad wrote:

[quote=“OnlyOneRule, post:1, topic:267993”]Get some celotape and and lollypop stick. Then stick your toe to the toe next to it, with the stick between each toe. Make sure you keep it straight and don’t tighten it soo much that it’s forced to bend.

I’ve broken plenty of things. Shoulder, wrists a few times, few fingers. The first time I broke a finger I went to the hospital. The other few times I couldn’t be botherd waiting in a smelly casualty. So did some DIY. Worked just fine.

If It it’s badly bruised and bent. I’d go to a hospital though.[/quote]

you must be a cripple…

item.title: I broke my toe
item.dc:creator: @srt8 srt8
item.description:
@srt8 wrote:

It is recommended you go to the doctor to get an xray to make sure there aren’t any bad fractures. All they would do is set it and splint it. When you wrap it, make sure you put a cotton ball or a wad of tissue between the toes so when it heals it won’t always lean that way. It will probably hurt for a month or so.

Read full topic
